      "lesson title": "AI in Clinical Decisions: When “Helpful” Becomes Harmful",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "Artificial intelligence tools are increasingly being used to support clinical decision-making, but understanding their limitations is just as important as recognising their potential. This lesson explores the real risks that arise when healthcare professionals place too much trust in AI-generated diagnoses or treatment recommendations. We will examine how AI systems can produce plausible-sounding but incorrect outputs, and why factors such as biased training data, lack of clinical context, and overconfidence in results can lead to patient harm. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to use AI tools responsibly as one part of a broader clinical process, rather than as a replacement for professional judgement.",
