          "slidecontent": "• Unable to weigh up the full clinical picture the way an experienced clinician can\n• Misses subtle cues\n• No access to a patient's tone, body language, or lived history\n• Struggles with rare or atypical presentations that fall outside its training data\n• Cannot account for local protocols, resource availability, or patient values\n• Pattern-matching is not the same as clinical judgement"
